Under President Irwin in 1977, there arose plans to relocate the college to a {{convert|125|acre|m2|sing=on}} parcel of land in [[Newtown Square, Pennsylvania]], by purchasing the faltering Charles E. Ellis School for Girls.<ref>{{cite news 
  | last = 
  | first = 
  | coauthors = 
