[[Image:Adamsexecutivecenter.jpg|thumb|right|Front entrance to the Adams Executive Center in Quincy]]

In 1995, the college tried relocating once more, this time by purchasing the former {{convert|56|acre|m2|sing=on}} campus of the Boston School for the Deaf in [[Randolph, Massachusetts]] from the [[Sisters of St. Joseph]], but the deal fell through despite support from the town [[selectmen]].<ref>{{cite news 
