===Extracurriculars===

[[Image:AngellhallwindowsENC.jpg|thumb|right|The stained glass windows of Angell Chapel in Angell Hall]]

There are no [[fraternities]] or [[sororities]] on campus, but there are Greek "societies". Until 2002, there were four societies based on intramural sports competition, which included the "[[Kappa]] Cougars", the "[[Sigma]] Stallions", and the "[[Zeta]] Warriors". New societies were formed in 2007 and originally numbered eight but were reduced to four again in 2008. Current membership is primarily based on residency, but includes faculty and staff.

There has been an Honors Scholar Society since 1936,<ref name="Cameron 1968 309">{{cite book
  | last = Cameron
  | first = James R.
  | authorlink = James R. Cameron
  | coauthors = 
  | title = Eastern Nazarene College<U+2014>The First Fifty Years, 1900-1950
  | publisher = Nazarene Publishing House
  | year = 1968
  | location = Kansas City
  | url = 
  | doi = 
  | id = 
  | isbn =
  | page = 309 }}</ref> and there are various national honors societies (''[[Phi Alpha Theta]]'' for history majors, ''Phi Delta Lambda'' for Nazarene scholars,<ref>{{cite book
  | last = Cameron
  | first = James R.
  | authorlink = James R. Cameron
  | coauthors = 
  | title = Eastern Nazarene College<U+2014>The First Fifty Years, 1900-1950
  | publisher = Nazarene Publishing House
  | year = 1968
  | location = Kansas City
  | url = 
  | doi = 
  | id = 
  | isbn =
  | page = 309 }} Organized in 1940 at the [[List_of_Church_of_the_Nazarene_conventions#General_Assembly|Nazarene General Assembly]].</ref> ''[[Psi Chi]]'' for psychology majors, etc.). Students participate in the [[Student Government Association]] (SGA), Class Council, Students for Social Justice,<ref name="park">{{cite news 
  | last = Kim
  | first = Eunice
  | coauthors = 
  | title = ENC students to clean up park in North Weymouth
