  | pages = 
  | language = 
  | publisher = 
  | date = April 8, 2006
  | url = 
  | accessdate = July 24, 2009}}</ref> academic clubs (''[[Beta Phi Mu]]'' Shrader Club, Biology Club, History Club, etc.), and club sports. The student-run [[newspaper]] is "The Veritas News", since 1933 and regularly published since 1936, and the student-developed [[yearbook]] has been the ''Nautilus'' since 1922.<ref>{{cite book
  | last = Cameron
  | first = James R.
  | authorlink = James R. Cameron
  | coauthors = 
  | title = Eastern Nazarene College<U+2014>The First Fifty Years, 1900-1950
  | publisher = Nazarene Publishing House
  | year = 1968
  | location = Kansas City
  | url = 
  | doi = 
  | id = 
  | isbn =
  | page = 158 }}</ref>

There are [[vocal music|vocal]] and [[instrumental]] [[musical ensemble|ensembles]], including the [[A capella|A Cappella]] Choir,<ref>{{cite web
