  | date = August 1, 2004
  | url = 
  | accessdate = }}</ref> Alumnus Edward Thomas Dell, Jr. was a published author, the editor of ''The Episcopalian'' from 1968 to 1973, and founder of two magazines, and he kept a running correspondence with [[C. S. Lewis]], which is now archived in the [[Bodleian Library]] and at [[Wheaton College (Illinois)|Wheaton College]].<ref>{{cite book
  | last =  Lewis
  | first = Clive Staples
