  | format = PDF
  | doi = 
  | accessdate = 2009-05-13}}</ref> Carl Crouthamel earned his doctorate at the [[University of Chicago]] after graduating from ENC, is famous for his work with [[Enrico Fermi]] on the U.S. project that produced the first [[atomic bomb]], started the first program to build a [[Gamma-ray astronomy|gamma ray lens for use in astronomy]], and has worked for the [[Argonne National Laboratory]].<ref>{{cite news 
  | last = Crowley
  | first = Elizabeth
  | coauthors = 
